# Environment variables

## Frontend (Vercel / local `.env`)

```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
VITE_SITE_URL=https://www.kcdesignmfg.com
VITE_GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
VITE_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=your_clarity_project_id
VITE_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=your_google_verification_token
```

Get these from **Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API**.

Only the **anon** key belongs in the frontend. Never put the service role key in Vite env vars.

---

## Supabase Edge Function secrets

Set in **Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets** (or via CLI):

```env
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxx
RFQ_NOTIFICATION_TO=info@kcdesignmfg.com
RFQ_FROM_EMAIL=K&C Design and Manufacturing <no-reply@your-verified-domain.com>
RFQ_REPLY_TO=info@kcdesignmfg.com
RFQ_NOTIFICATION_FROM=K&C RFQ <rfq@your-verified-domain.com>
FACTORAOS_INTAKE_ENDPOINT=https://your-factoraos-instance.com/api/crm/intake
FACTORAOS_INTAKE_API_KEY=your_factoraos_intake_api_key
```

- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — server-side only; used to read RFQ records and file metadata
- `RESEND_API_KEY` — from [resend.com](https://resend.com); used to email K&C and customers when an RFQ is submitted
- `RFQ_FROM_EMAIL` — verified sender for customer confirmation emails (falls back to `RFQ_NOTIFICATION_FROM`, then Resend onboarding address for local testing)
- `RFQ_REPLY_TO` — reply-to address on customer confirmation emails

---

## Setup checklist

1. Create a Supabase project
2. Run migrations:
   - `supabase/migrations/001_create_rfq_requests.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/002_create_admin_profiles_and_rfq_policies.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/004_add_quote_email_drafts_manual_send_tracking.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/007_add_rfq_reference_number.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/008_add_rfq_customer_confirmation_email_tracking.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/009_add_public_rfq_status_lookup.sql`
   - `supabase/migrations/010_add_customer_status_update_email_workflow.sql`
3. Create an admin user in Supabase Auth (Dashboard → Authentication → Users)
4. Seed the admin profile (see comments in migration 002)
5. Deploy edge functions:
   - `supabase functions deploy send-rfq-notification`
   - `supabase functions deploy public-rfq-status-lookup`
   - `supabase functions deploy send-customer-status-update`
   - `supabase functions deploy send-rfq-to-factoraos`
6. Add Edge Function secrets listed above
7. Add frontend env vars to Vercel (or local `.env`)
8. Deploy the Vite site
9. Sign in at `/admin/login` with your approved admin account

---

## RFQ workflow

1. Visitor submits form → insert `rfq_requests`
2. Files upload to private bucket `rfq-files` at `rfq/{id}/{timestamp}-{filename}`
3. File metadata saved to `rfq_files`
4. Edge Function `send-rfq-notification` emails `info@kcdesignmfg.com` and sends a customer confirmation email via Resend
